<div class="content" name="TRUSTED_DOMAIN_SUPPORTED_ENCRYPTION_TYPES" uuid="7c519a64-3dc1-4be6-a17d-76817cff6e39"><p>The TRUSTED_DOMAIN_SUPPORTED_ENCRYPTION_TYPES structure is
used to present the encryption types that are allowed through a <span><a href="31ca2a31-0be4-4773-bcef-05ad6cd3ccfb#gt_5ee032d0-d944-4acb-bbb5-b1cfc7df6db6" data-linktype="relative-path">trust</a></span>.</p><dl>
<dd>
<div><pre> typedef struct _TRUSTED_DOMAIN_SUPPORTED_ENCRYPTION_TYPES {
   unsigned long SupportedEncryptionTypes;
 } TRUSTED_DOMAIN_SUPPORTED_ENCRYPTION_TYPES,
  *PTRUSTED_DOMAIN_SUPPORTED_ENCRYPTION_TYPES;
</pre></div>
</dd></dl><p><b>SupportedEncryptionTypes:</b>  This
field contains bitmapped values that define the encryption types supported by
